ENTRY       EC 4.2.99.22                Enzyme
NAME        tuliposide A-converting enzyme;
            tuliposide-converting enzyme;
            6-O-(4'-hydroxy-2'-methylenebutyryl)-D-glucose acyltransferase (lactone-forming);
            TCA;
            TCEA
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Other carbon-oxygen lyases
SYSNAME     6-tuliposide A D-glucose-lyase (tulipalin A forming)
REACTION    6-tuliposide A = tulipalin A + D-glucose [RN:R10494]
ALL_REAC    R10494
SUBSTRATE   6-tuliposide A [CPD:C20577]
PRODUCT     tulipalin A [CPD:C20578];
            D-glucose [CPD:C00031]
COMMENT     Isolated from the plant Tulipa gesneriana (tulip). The reaction is an intramolecular transesterification producing the lactone. The enzyme also has a weak activity with 6-tuliposide B and 6-O-benzoyl-D-glucose.
HISTORY     EC 4.2.99.22 created 2013
